snippet.title: BURN IT DOWN (this is an original)
snippet.description:
I wrote this song JUST FOR YOU but also for anyone who's ever beat you to a breakup

soundcloud: amberlaundry
instagram: scamberlandry
twitter: 4mberland


LYRICS


What do you see
in the smoke rising from the old ash tree
warm, golden leak
spilling our guts into the next century


I’ll tell you what i heard
in the cinders of crackling branches
names intertwined 
a vessel encircled so amorously 


who else do you think wanted to burn it down
who else would it be
oh dear god i wish it was me


who will i be
bitterness clung to what used to be
the roots on the old ash tree
are all of what happened before you and me


but who else do you think wanted to burn it down
who else would it be
oh god i wish it was me


we saw it was breaking before it was burning
rolling our eyes back and faithful returning
home is where the matches are 
and you found them first 


who else do you think wanted to burn it down 
who else would it be
oh god i wish it was me




instagram: @scamberlandry
twitter: @amberl4nd
 
:)
